delete files except source files : make clean
    NOTE: all files whose name matches '*.log' will be deleted!

compile moecompiler : make -j4 opti="-O2" compiler
compile moecompiler and run : make -j4 opti="-O2" run args="testcase.sysy -S -o testcase.s"
run directly : ./compiler testcase.sysy -S -o testcase.s

command line options :
    By default, all argument neither without prefix of '-' or '--' nor followed by option
    will be interpreted as files to compile.
    (For now, compiler is designed to compile one file for once)
    
    [-d] : debug option
        /*  This option will enable debug information to be created.
         *  This will also enable default mdb which prints information to stdou. 
         */
    [-S] : assemble option
        /* if and only if command line has this option, compiler will compile files provided.
         * */
        [-o <ofiledir> ] (needed) : specify output file directory. 

    [-t] : unit test option
        /*  Let compiler do unit test. 
         *  All arguments after it will be considered as the settings of unit test. 
         *  So if you want to print debug info, let '-d' come before '-t'
         *  All test names should be placed in the end.
         *  e.g : ./compiler -d -t -p exprTest regexSwitchTest 
         * */
        [-p] : This option let compiler print all availible unit tests to stdout before testing.


        
    

